<TITLE> Garments workers take to streets over Eid arrears </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com)  Workers of a Rampura garments factory took to the streets for nearly 12 hours Friday to demand Eid bonuses and wages six days after the festival, police officials said. The demonstrating workers blocked roads and damaged a motor vehicle in the Rampura area of the city. Police and RAB later brought the situation under control. Ramna thana second officer Golam Mahfiz said Voyager Garments' management failed to pay wages and bonuses to factory workers by Eid as promised. They rescheduled the payment date to Friday. Factory workers took to the streets when Voyager Garments' management failed to pay arrears a second time. Factory management and workers reached an agreement in the presence of law enforcement personnel. The Voyager Garments has promised to pay its workers' arrears by October
